  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am using a Moto G, and it failed to download the OTA update of Android due to a network error. Now what can I do to get it updated?",
  "response": "If your Moto G failed to download the Over-the-Air (OTA) update due to a network error, there are several steps you can follow to try and successfully update your device:\n\n1. **Check Your Internet Connection**: \n   Ensure that you have a stable and strong Wi-Fi connection. OTA updates are often large files and require a consistent internet connection.\n\n2. **Restart Your Device**: \n   Sometimes, a simple restart can resolve temporary issues related to network or system errors. Power off your phone and turn it back on again.\n\n3. **Clear Cache**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Storage** > **Cached data** and clear the cache. This can sometimes resolve issues with downloading updates.\n\n4. **Free Some Storage Space**:\n   Make sure your phone has enough storage space to download the update. Go to **Settings** > **Storage**, and if necessary, delete some files or apps to free up space.\n\n5. **Try Again**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **System** > **Software update** and attempt to download the update again.\n\n6. **Update Using a Different Wi-Fi Network**:\n   If possible, connect to a different Wi-Fi network and try downloading the update. Sometimes network-specific issues can prevent successful downloads.\n\n7. **Update via Computer**:\n   Some smartphone manufacturers provide tools for updating software via a computer. Check Moto's support website to see if there is a desktop application (like Motorola Device Manager) that you can use to download and install the update.\n\n8. **Factory Reset**:\n   As a last resort, you could perform a factory reset on your device before attempting the update again. However, make sure to back up your data first as this will erase everything on your phone.\n   - Go to **Settings** > **System** > **Reset options** > **Erase all data (factory reset)**.\n\n9. **Contact Support**:\n   If none of the above steps work, you may want to reach out to Motorola's customer support for further assistance. They might be able to provide specific solutions or advice.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to resolve the issue and successfully update your Moto G.",
